<paragraph id="FE79CD20FF8EFFD4FC9176EEDD4FFBE2" blockId="63.[794,1399,969,1121]" pageId="63" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="CCB21132FF8EFFD4FC9176EEDBF1FC62" bold="true" box="[794,905,969,993]" pageId="63" pageNumber="76">Comment</emphasis>
: This species has been recorded only from Borneo. The proximal portion of the spermathecal capsule of the above female is of slightly different shape than that illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF8EFFD4FB90710EDCD9FBC2" author="PACE, R." box="[1051,1185,1065,1089]" pageId="63" pageNumber="76" pagination="727 - 794" refId="ref78194" refString="PACE, R. 2014: Aleocharinae from Sabah (Borneo) collected by Guillaume de Rougemont (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 46 (1): 727 - 794." type="journal article" year="2014">PACE (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, but the abdominal tergite VIII is identical (see 
<bibRefCitation id="9A57B0D1FF8EFFD4FBCA716EDCCBFBE2" author="PACE, R." box="[1089,1203,1097,1121]" pageId="63" pageNumber="76" pagination="727 - 794" refId="ref78194" refString="PACE, R. 2014: Aleocharinae from Sabah (Borneo) collected by Guillaume de Rougemont (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 46 (1): 727 - 794." type="journal article" year="2014">PACE 2014</bibRefCitation>
: figure 124).
</paragraph>
